cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NA

The paper deals with depth acquisition and estimation using computer vision techniques, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a method for sparse representation and sampling, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method uses an alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM), which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of wavelets and contourlets, which are common tools in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a randomized sampling scheme, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
